Job Description:
Transfer Pricing Practice:
• Manage & support the Transfer Pricing Team in Hanoi Office to complete the on-going TP engagements to be assigned by Partners and Directors from time to time;
• Develop a training program for the TP teams in Hanoi;
• Provide periodically technical updates and training on international TP practices and local regulations;
• Develop the TP Team in Hanoi in personnel, technical ability, developing standard procedures for TP engagements.
Business Development for TP practice:
• Demonstrates an understanding of the firm's products, services and capabilities specifically on TP Practice and takes an active role in cross selling;
• Builds an understanding of the potential for selling into clients;
• Seeks to participate in business development activities and contributes to sales pitches, for own team as well as the wider firm;
• Builds a rapport with the individual client and develops a clear and detailed understanding of the business and client expectations;
• Meets clients’ demands, keeping them up to date with progress and engenders trust and respect.

Job Requirements:
Qualifications/Skills
• Bachelor’s degree or post-graduate degree in accounting, tax, law or corporate finance;
• Be familiar with Vietnam’s transfer pricing regulations, APA, OECD guidelines and BEPS.
• Minimum of 8 year working experience in transfer pricing work;
• Fluency in English, both speaking and writing;
• Good working knowledge of MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint;
• Good project management, teamwork, interpersonal and communications skill;
• Holding VTCA, CPA, ACCA, CPAA, ICAEW, TP Certificates will be a plus.

Job Description:
- Lập biện pháp thi công cho từng dự án, HSMT.
